==English==
===Etymology===
Possibly named after the Bogan River area in Australia.

===Noun===
'''bogan''' (''plural'' '''bogans''')

#(''Australian'') A person who is, or is perceived to be, of a white or [[indigenous]] lower class background. The term excludes Australians who belong to ethnic groups that were established relatively recently. The stereotype includes having speech and [[mannerism]]s that are considered to denote poor education and upbringing, and having an intrest in Australian build cars(eg. Holdens, Fords,etc.) and Heavy metal music. Its meaning is more or less analagous to the USamerican [[Redneck]].
#(''New Zealand'') A member of a lower [[socioeconomic]] group historically classified by the wearing of black [[jumper]]s, black [[T-shirt]]s decorated with designs including such bands as Led Zeppelin, The Doors and Nirvana or favourite drinks such as Jack Daniels or Jim Beam. Bogans often drive larger cars and are often referred to as [[petrolhead]]s.
#(''North Western Ontario'') A slang word for a Native person typically percieved with gangster ties
====Synonyms====
*(''uncool young person''): [[dag]] (''Australia'')
*(''in New Zealand sense''): [[bevan]] (''Queensland, Australia''), [[westy]] ''or'' [[westie]] (''Australia, especially Sydney'')

